WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:03.287
OLIVER:
Previously on Smallville:

00:03.461 --> 00:04.917
KARA:
A darkness has come to Earth.

00:05.130 --> 00:06.870
This isn't your ﬁght.

00:07.090 --> 00:09.001
I'm not gonna stand here
and do nothing.

00:09.259 --> 00:12.251
KARA: You've been on Earth all this time
and you can't even ﬂy.

00:13.346 --> 00:18.261
The woman that I, uh— That I love,
she sacriﬁced everything to protect me.

00:18.435 --> 00:22.269
First I'll eat, and then I'll molt
and then I'll mate.

00:23.648 --> 00:28.108
I am the Brain InterActive Construct.
Do not underestimate me.

00:29.571 --> 00:30.731
[YELLS]

00:32.365 --> 00:35.277
It is safer if you stay in the shadows.
It's safer for all heroes.

00:35.452 --> 00:38.694
Maybe people deserve to know the truth.
I am Green Arrow.

00:40.415 --> 00:43.657
GODFREY:
There is darkness in you and great power.

00:43.877 --> 00:46.744
You're afraid
you'll never be the hero you wanna be.

00:46.921 --> 00:50.163
JOR—EL:
You will never be Earth's savoir.

01:01.978 --> 01:03.889
Good question.

01:14.866 --> 01:17.152
Maybe you were right, Jor-El.

01:19.454 --> 01:21.615
Maybe I'm not the one.

01:22.415 --> 01:23.495
Maybe none of us are.

01:25.502 --> 01:27.493
[DOOR OPENS]

01:31.841 --> 01:35.880
Lois. Hey, I'm sorry,
I've kind of been out of it lately.

01:36.054 --> 01:37.385
I left you a message.

01:37.555 --> 01:39.841
Yeah, three days ago.
You feeling better?

01:42.102 --> 01:43.592
Well, no worries.

01:43.770 --> 01:45.852
You didn't miss anything
in the news department.

01:46.022 --> 01:47.137
CLARK:
Okay.

01:47.357 --> 01:49.939
Seems the Blur took
a little vacation this week too.

01:51.569 --> 01:53.946
-There must be something going around.
-Hmm.

01:58.743 --> 02:00.859
Hero haters.

02:01.037 --> 02:04.279
Just when you think the world
couldn't get more upside-down, right?

02:06.376 --> 02:09.789
People probably don't wanna put their hope
in someone who's gonna let them down.

02:16.553 --> 02:19.841
He never would let us down.

02:20.014 --> 02:22.300
The Blur, I mean.

02:23.184 --> 02:25.300
And this person, for one,
is gonna stand by her hero...

02:25.478 --> 02:29.221
-...no matter how much mud they sling.
-Why?

02:30.692 --> 02:34.025
Because that's what you do
when you believe in someone.

02:38.658 --> 02:41.775
You know what you need?
A pick-me-up.

02:44.539 --> 02:45.654
[CH UCKLES]

02:45.832 --> 02:49.495
Thanks, Lois, but I don't think playing
quarterback is gonna make my day.

02:49.669 --> 02:51.079
Depends on the cheerleader.

02:53.214 --> 02:56.331
Come on, did you forget?
Tomorrow's our Smallville High reunion.

02:58.428 --> 03:00.384
-Did you say our reunion?
-Yes.

03:00.555 --> 03:03.638
-You were enrolled there for, like—
-Twenty-three days.

03:04.559 --> 03:07.517
-You showed up for ﬁve.
-That's a record in my book.

03:07.687 --> 03:10.269
Smallville's the closest thing to a past
this military brat has.

03:10.440 --> 03:12.931
And I am not gonna miss it.

03:13.943 --> 03:16.935
We don't have to be dating
to show up at a reunion together.

03:18.948 --> 03:21.439
There's a lot
of memories there for me, I—

03:21.618 --> 03:23.700
Come on, Clark,
it would mean a lot to me.

03:24.245 --> 03:29.956
Seeing all those familiar faces.
It's like I had a place, like I ﬁt in.

03:30.585 --> 03:31.791
And you....

03:31.961 --> 03:36.546
I mean, you put the "Smallville"
in Smallville, Smallville.

03:37.008 --> 03:39.374
Besides, what's the worst thing
that could happen?

03:49.562 --> 03:54.556
I've wasted a decade picking up
the pieces from meteor-mutant students.

03:56.194 --> 04:00.028
"How do I get into college
with a criminal record?"

04:00.657 --> 04:03.194
You can't, freak.

04:04.077 --> 04:09.367
You see, I have spent years hearing
their stories.

04:09.540 --> 04:10.575
And— And no—

04:10.750 --> 04:16.211
No matter how crazy they are,
they always mention one person.

04:17.548 --> 04:18.583
You.

04:22.929 --> 04:25.591
Clark Kent.

04:25.765 --> 04:30.225
So nice of you to come back
to the reunion, save me a trip.

04:30.395 --> 04:36.311
Looks like your bill is up
and it is time for you to pay.

04:48.162 --> 04:51.245
It's time to move on from the past.

04:51.666 --> 04:53.577
Leave Clark Kent to me.

05:58.274 --> 06:01.061
Guess I just haven't been back
in a while.

06:02.779 --> 06:04.269
[CHATTERING]

06:05.990 --> 06:10.609
Oh. There's Eddie from chem class.
Hey.

06:10.787 --> 06:13.824
Oh, and Jake and the cupcake girl
are together now.

06:15.333 --> 06:18.575
Hi. Sally "Pep Rally" Dickinson
has put on a few.

06:18.753 --> 06:21.711
Lois, I don't really have
a good feeling about all this.

06:27.762 --> 06:31.220
Nietzsche? I didn't realize
you had a dark side, Clark.

06:33.518 --> 06:36.726
-Well, doesn't everybody?
-Yeah, I guess so.

06:40.149 --> 06:43.687
So, what are you, man or superman?

06:55.164 --> 06:57.655
Well, look who it is. Clark Kent.

06:58.626 --> 07:01.163
Have I got something for you.

07:01.796 --> 07:03.787
A hug.

07:05.133 --> 07:06.589
Um, thanks.

07:06.759 --> 07:10.126
Oh, now, don't leave early.
We've got a special treat for you.

07:14.183 --> 07:15.218
A couple more hugs...

07:15.393 --> 07:18.726
...and maybe you'll have
the bah-humbugs squeezed out of you.

07:19.021 --> 07:20.682
[CAR APPROACHES]

07:38.124 --> 07:39.739
Welcome back. Isn't this great?

07:39.917 --> 07:42.374
l have the whole day
mapped out for you.

07:43.045 --> 07:45.001
Adelia. Laney.

07:45.173 --> 07:47.585
-Lois Lane. Chess Club?
ADELIA: Uh....

07:47.758 --> 07:49.885
| sat through an entire game once?

07:50.052 --> 07:52.464
ADELIA: Whatever.
GIRL: Come on, let's go.

07:53.055 --> 07:54.636
Mark.

07:55.099 --> 07:57.215
Hey, Mark. Smoking times, huh?

07:59.187 --> 08:00.222
Should I know you?

08:00.438 --> 08:02.724
Like you don't remember
behind the gym on a smoke break?

08:02.899 --> 08:05.515
I mean,
I was chewing gum at the time, but—

08:05.693 --> 08:07.854
Really? Nothing.

08:08.029 --> 08:10.520
Hey, Lois. Let's, um, go inside.

08:13.201 --> 08:14.611
SUZANNE:
Clark.

08:15.161 --> 08:17.243
Ha, ha. I can't believe you're here.

08:17.413 --> 08:19.529
What happened to the bumbling nerd?

08:24.712 --> 08:25.827
Susan Capra.

08:26.672 --> 08:31.541
Suzanne, actually.
You always mixed us up.

08:31.719 --> 08:33.675
Well, you haven't changed a bit.

08:34.889 --> 08:35.969
Bak, bak, Crow.

08:36.974 --> 08:38.054
Oh.

08:39.227 --> 08:41.969
-Oh. Here you go.
-Thank you.

08:43.940 --> 08:45.350
Are you his plus one?

08:46.108 --> 08:47.268
[CH UCKLES]

08:51.072 --> 08:52.687
I went to school here, people.

08:58.454 --> 09:01.787
Lane. Lane, Lane, Lane.

09:05.920 --> 09:06.955
[CLEARS THROAT]

09:07.129 --> 09:08.630
Lang.

09:11.175 --> 09:14.167
Wow, old ﬂames.

09:17.014 --> 09:20.757
I should've known this would happen.
I haven't seen her since...

09:20.935 --> 09:23.972
...your barn when we were about to--

09:25.898 --> 09:27.889
She's not coming.

09:30.152 --> 09:32.985
| forgot how many memories
you have here.

09:50.339 --> 09:53.502
CHLOE: It started out as a scrapbook
and just kind of mutated.

09:53.676 --> 09:55.041
CLARK:
What is it?

09:55.219 --> 09:58.256
I call it the Wall of Weird.

10:01.100 --> 10:02.135
So, what do you think?

10:03.269 --> 10:04.725
LOIS:
Clark.

10:08.024 --> 10:09.059
I'm
sorry

10:11.902 --> 10:14.359
Maybe I shouldn't have
brought you back here.

10:15.740 --> 10:18.447
ZOE:
Oh, my God.

10:18.659 --> 10:22.277
-You were friends with Chloe Sullivan.
-Yeah, what happened to her?

10:22.496 --> 10:25.784
She was the rising star of the
Daily Planet like she always dreamed.

10:26.000 --> 10:27.991
-And now—
-lt's like she just vanished.

10:28.169 --> 10:30.706
Like someone found out
that she knew too much.

10:31.756 --> 10:35.294
Looks like somebody took a bite
out of Chloe's conspiracy cookie.

10:35.468 --> 10:38.551
I'm sorry to disappoint you,
but Chloe couldn't make it.

10:40.473 --> 10:43.715
Wait a minute, I know you.
You're Lois Lane.

10:43.934 --> 10:45.845
Yes, thank you.

10:46.062 --> 10:48.223
You dated the Green Arrow,
a.k.a. Oliver....

10:48.689 --> 10:50.304
-Oliver Queen.
-Oliver Queen.

10:52.401 --> 10:54.813
What's it like
to date a real superhero?

10:55.279 --> 10:58.396
It-- It was really quick, just a ﬂash.

10:58.574 --> 11:02.237
But I would date one again
in a heartbeat.

11:03.162 --> 11:06.746
-So this is all that's left of the Torch?
-Are you kidding?

11:07.249 --> 11:09.410
We carry the Torch with us every day.

11:09.585 --> 11:12.327
Everything you need to know about
the mysterious and unexplained.

11:12.546 --> 11:14.707
The Wall of Weird has gone viral.

11:19.053 --> 11:21.840
-The Blur.
-What?

11:23.015 --> 11:25.392
Okay, promise not to tell anyone.

11:25.559 --> 11:28.221
Okay, we have a theory
that the Blur was born...

11:28.396 --> 11:31.229
-And raised in Smallville.
-...in Smallville.

11:31.399 --> 11:36.018
Okay, I think your virtual weird wall
has left you a pushpin short.

11:36.237 --> 11:37.977
You're the one who writes about him.

11:38.155 --> 11:40.862
You seriously never considered
that all of these miraculous saves...

11:41.033 --> 11:42.694
...that Chloe wrote about in the Torch...

11:42.868 --> 11:45.575
...started right before
the Blur showed up in Metropolis?

11:45.746 --> 11:48.283
I wouldn't waste
any more time on the Blur.

11:48.791 --> 11:52.409
Seems like he's gone away
and I'm not so sure he'll be back.

11:53.045 --> 11:57.755
I think what Clark is trying to say,
is that it's great that the Blur...

11:57.967 --> 12:01.459
...has been there to be a role model
for kids like you to look up to.

12:01.679 --> 12:03.965
I mean, how many people in the world
has he inspired?

12:04.181 --> 12:07.890
Exactly. Maybe it's a good thing
he didn't show up for the reunion.

12:08.060 --> 12:12.099
-He would've stolen your thunder, Clark.
-What thunder?

12:14.608 --> 12:19.022
SUSAN: Okay, Crows, give it up for your
alumni homecoming king, Clark Kent.

12:19.196 --> 12:20.402
[BAND PLAYING AND ALUMNI CHEERING]

12:20.573 --> 12:23.064
Now, this is the homecoming
I'm talking about.

12:23.242 --> 12:27.281
Thank God you squeaked out that state
championship in your senior year.

12:46.015 --> 12:48.802
CHEERLEADERS:
One! Two! Three!

12:48.976 --> 12:50.807
Come on, Crows!

13:17.963 --> 13:23.799
My sincere apologies for interrupting
this festive trip down memory lane.

13:24.261 --> 13:27.924
-Brainiac. I thought we destroyed you.
-Hmm.

13:28.098 --> 13:30.134
Whatever you want,
leave these people out of it.

13:30.351 --> 13:33.343
Oh, don't worry,
I'm only here for you.

13:35.731 --> 13:38.268
I wanted to slow things down.

13:38.442 --> 13:41.104
Make sure you can soak
in this special moment.

13:43.197 --> 13:45.984
And what's so special
about this moment?

13:46.200 --> 13:49.533
This is the moment
that your life changes forever.

14:09.056 --> 14:11.968
I don't know if you're a ghost or
the darkness Jor-El warned me about...

14:12.142 --> 14:14.804
...but this will come to an end
just like it did the last time.

14:14.979 --> 14:18.016
-I hope so, for your sake.
-For my sake?

14:18.190 --> 14:20.272
You sent the person that I love away.

14:20.442 --> 14:23.434
You tried to destroy Chloe,
you tried to destroy the world.

14:23.654 --> 14:28.398
And you saved me from all that, Kal-El.
I've come back to do the same for you.

14:29.326 --> 14:32.659
The Legion? You're from the future.

14:36.250 --> 14:38.241
-What did you do to them?
-I joined them.

14:38.878 --> 14:41.415
In the 31st century,
I'm known as Brainiac 5.

14:41.589 --> 14:43.545
The ring, time travel, all my creations.

14:43.716 --> 14:46.799
I brought the Legion
into a new realm of heroism.

14:46.969 --> 14:51.884
-They helped me destroy you.
-No, they helped you cure me.

14:53.434 --> 14:56.847
The problem is, Kal-El,
you and I aren't very different.

14:57.021 --> 14:59.637
We were both created
in one way or another by Jor-El.

14:59.815 --> 15:05.230
Both intended to save civilizations,
to bring peace to a brutal world.

15:05.404 --> 15:10.148
But neither of us
was immune to corruption, to darkness.

15:10.326 --> 15:12.282
And what does that mean?

15:12.661 --> 15:14.947
Everyone's telling me
I've a darkness within me.

15:15.122 --> 15:18.580
But I don't understand what it is
or how I'm supposed to change it.

15:20.336 --> 15:22.668
You destroyed cities.

15:23.672 --> 15:27.290
I may not make the right decisions,
but at least I'm trying to save people.

15:27.468 --> 15:31.962
Then let me show you, Kal-El.
We can't always see it in ourselves.

15:33.432 --> 15:35.593
My corruption started
with a nanobyte.

15:35.768 --> 15:37.133
[BRAINIAC SCOFFS]

15:37.311 --> 15:41.224
Smaller than the eye can see.
But that's all it took.

15:46.737 --> 15:48.978
My father's funeral.

15:50.491 --> 15:52.356
[FUNERAL BELL RINGING IN DISTANCE]

16:01.001 --> 16:04.619
If you're trying to save me somehow,
why show me this?

16:05.339 --> 16:07.455
Because this was a deﬁning moment
for you.

16:07.633 --> 16:09.248
Perhaps the deﬁning moment.

16:09.760 --> 16:12.502
The day that you started
to blame yourself.

16:13.055 --> 16:15.216
Why wouldn't I?

16:15.683 --> 16:19.175
I chose to change fate.
It was my fault that he died.

16:19.353 --> 16:20.889
Was it?

16:29.947 --> 16:30.982
Dad.

16:31.156 --> 16:34.114
JONATHAN:
I won't let you destroy my family.

16:36.203 --> 16:37.659
[GRUNTS]

16:38.539 --> 16:41.076
We can withstand anything
you bring down on us.

16:41.834 --> 16:43.165
Because we have each other.

16:43.794 --> 16:47.378
That's what will always separate
the Kents from the Luthors.

16:48.882 --> 16:50.838
Now, why don't you get—?

16:51.760 --> 16:54.376
-You can't change his fate.
-He was just protecting me.

16:54.555 --> 16:57.262
And that was his choice.

16:57.558 --> 16:59.219
Whether it happens
this day or any other...

16:59.393 --> 17:01.258
...Jonathan set his own destiny
into the motion.

17:01.437 --> 17:02.893
You know that.

17:03.272 --> 17:05.684
You just won't let yourself believe it.

17:12.740 --> 17:16.824
-Why won't you forgive yourself?
-He didn't have a choice.

17:17.077 --> 17:19.693
He's my father, of course
he'd sacriﬁce anything to protect me.

17:19.872 --> 17:22.534
BRAINIAC:
We always have a choice, Kal-El.

17:23.208 --> 17:26.575
Your father didn't have
to care for you the way he did.

17:26.754 --> 17:29.791
Yet still he made
that choice every day he was with you.

17:29.965 --> 17:32.422
He chose to be your protector.

17:33.594 --> 17:36.506
Just as you've chosen
to be the Earth's protector.

17:37.347 --> 17:40.054
Nobody forced that on you,
yet you embraced it.

17:40.225 --> 17:42.307
Nobody made that choice for you.

17:42.770 --> 17:46.433
We all choose our own fate.

17:48.942 --> 17:51.433
NEWSWOMAN [ON TV]:
Fans and protestors alike are in an outcry...

17:51.612 --> 17:54.319
...for the playboy-tumed-Green Arrow
Oliver Queen...

17:54.490 --> 17:56.526
...who dropped
his shocking announcement...

17:56.700 --> 17:58.565
...and has since vanished from society.

17:58.744 --> 18:02.453
MAN: lgot kids. What happens when they
grow up and wanna be vigilantes like him?

18:03.165 --> 18:05.030
WOMAN:
It's great he 's helping people, but we....

18:05.250 --> 18:08.413
-This isn't a memory.
-No, it isn't, it's the present.

18:08.587 --> 18:11.044
MAN [ON TV]:
He lied to us all along.

18:11.215 --> 18:12.455
We can't trust him.

18:12.674 --> 18:14.665
If you're trying to make me feel guilty...

18:14.843 --> 18:17.801
...you just said
that we control our own fate.

18:17.971 --> 18:20.883
Oliver made his own decision
to come out to the public.

18:21.058 --> 18:23.390
He didn't think about what it would mean
to the rest of us.

18:23.602 --> 18:26.014
If you really are
the hero you say you are...

18:26.188 --> 18:28.474
...don't you think it's time
to face the public?

18:28.649 --> 18:31.186
We 're waiting for some answers.

18:32.027 --> 18:34.018
[HELICOPTER FLYING NEARBY]

18:36.073 --> 18:38.735
-Any calls?
SECRETARY: Where do you wanna start?

18:38.909 --> 18:41.366
CNN, BBC, Dr. Phil?

18:41.537 --> 18:43.744
No, I mean, any calls?

18:43.914 --> 18:49.159
SECRETARY: Oh, um, I'm sorry, sir.
Mr. Kent hasn't left a word.

19:01.140 --> 19:04.177
He's always so Oliver.
I didn't know that he needed me.

19:04.351 --> 19:06.137
But he does.

19:09.565 --> 19:14.400
I don't know how not returning his calls
amounts to some darkness within me.

19:14.945 --> 19:16.776
You don't see it?

19:17.489 --> 19:19.775
The darkness is the past.

19:19.950 --> 19:21.815
And you hold on to it and you dwell.

19:22.369 --> 19:26.078
You punish yourself and everyone
around you for past mistakes.

19:26.498 --> 19:29.365
We don't have the privilege
of mistakes.

19:29.543 --> 19:32.751
Even if we don't expect perfection
from ourselves, the world does.

19:32.921 --> 19:37.210
-You heard what they said.
-Then help Oliver be who he can be.

19:37.384 --> 19:40.968
Today, tomorrow.
Be there for him now.

19:41.180 --> 19:45.423
And stop punishing him for his past
with your silence and your distance.

19:46.310 --> 19:48.096
Let it go.

19:52.608 --> 19:54.940
[LIFEHOUSE'S "EVERYTHING"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

20:05.913 --> 20:08.529
Find me here

20:10.792 --> 20:13.454
And speak to me

20:14.004 --> 20:17.087
Which one of these has the punch in it,
if you know what I mean?

20:17.257 --> 20:21.296
MADDIE: Sorry?
We have lemonade and strawberryade.

20:21.511 --> 20:22.842
Yeah, but--

20:23.805 --> 20:24.840
Strawberryade.

20:26.266 --> 20:28.222
Lois, huh?

20:28.393 --> 20:31.681
-So who you here with?
-l'm an alum.

20:31.855 --> 20:33.595
That's leading me

20:33.774 --> 20:35.639
Lois Lane.

20:36.985 --> 20:39.852
To the place

20:40.072 --> 20:43.906
-l'm with Clark Kent.
MADDIE: Really?

20:44.117 --> 20:48.952
Oh, I just always thought Clark
was so dreamy, you know.

20:49.164 --> 20:52.452
That farm boy next door
turned local football hero.

20:52.626 --> 20:54.241
Doesn't get any bigger than that.

20:54.628 --> 20:58.120
Ha, ha. Funny, I always thought
he and Chloe were meant for each other.

20:58.298 --> 21:01.711
They had that whole
"best friend with hope of more" thing.

21:01.885 --> 21:06.720
-Chloe's my cousin.
-Yeah, but then there was Lana.

21:06.890 --> 21:11.600
I mean, how gorgeous can you get,
right? And hardworking.

21:11.770 --> 21:15.513
I mean, how many cheerleaders run
a coffee shop in high school?

21:15.691 --> 21:17.477
Lana and Clark were perfect.

21:17.651 --> 21:20.984
You know that ﬁrst love,
you never get over it.

21:21.154 --> 21:26.114
-I think I hear the veggie platter calling.
-Wait, so you're not hitched to Clark?

21:28.745 --> 21:29.860
Not exactly.

21:30.080 --> 21:32.662
-Are you engaged?
-Nope.

21:33.041 --> 21:36.124
Oh. How long
have you been seeing each other?

21:37.421 --> 21:41.664
Well, we're not, really. Right now.

21:42.801 --> 21:46.544
So you're the moth, not the ﬂame.

21:46.722 --> 21:49.429
And not be moved by you?

21:49.599 --> 21:51.555
Are you sure he likes you?

21:51.727 --> 21:56.391
Would you tell me, how could it be

21:56.565 --> 22:00.183
Any better than this?

22:00.360 --> 22:04.774
Correct me if I'm mistaken,
but you care about Lois, don't you?

22:04.990 --> 22:07.652
All I've ever done was protect her
after what happened with Lana.

22:07.826 --> 22:09.236
Interesting outcome.

22:10.203 --> 22:14.321
Lois doesn't seem
especially protected.

22:15.375 --> 22:18.742
You spend so much time dwelling on
the darkness of the past...

22:18.920 --> 22:22.208
...you're missing the present
that's right in front of your eyes.

22:22.549 --> 22:24.289
[DOOR OPENS]

22:29.765 --> 22:32.097
It's one of the people
I put away in high school.

22:32.309 --> 22:35.096
You don't know what he's capable of.
I need to get back.

22:35.270 --> 22:37.727
To do what? Weren't you about
to hang up your shield?

22:37.898 --> 22:39.479
I have a message for Clark Kent.

22:39.691 --> 22:41.556
-Give me the ring.
-Wait for the moment.

22:41.735 --> 22:44.477
No, Kal-El, you haven't learned
the full lesson!

22:49.451 --> 22:50.907
[ELEVATOR BELL RINGS]

22:51.912 --> 22:53.573
MAIL CLERK:
Whoa, buddy.

23:14.309 --> 23:16.220
-Hey, watch it.
-Lois.

23:16.395 --> 23:18.010
-How--?
-Not again.

23:18.188 --> 23:19.849
Come on.

23:23.193 --> 23:24.558
-Wait, did—?
-Seriously...

23:24.778 --> 23:27.986
...I know we agreed we would keep
our professional lives to ourselves...

23:28.156 --> 23:31.990
...but what kind of secret story
got you to dress-up day?

23:32.160 --> 23:33.366
Here, hold this.

23:33.537 --> 23:37.576
And I know that you don't like them, but
you decided you wanted to wear them.

23:37.791 --> 23:40.498
-And lucky for you, I have a spare. There.
-What--?

23:40.669 --> 23:43.581
Hey,
I know they are not fashion-fonivard.

23:43.797 --> 23:45.833
But if it ain't broke, honey,
don't ﬁx it.

23:49.219 --> 23:54.384
Seriously, Clark, I thought we agreed
on a Daily Planet dress code.

23:54.641 --> 23:55.676
[LOIS GROANS]

23:55.851 --> 23:58.183
Lois, wait. How did you get here?

23:58.395 --> 24:02.889
-I need to know about the reunion.
-We need to table this all until later.

24:03.525 --> 24:05.311
We cannot have
people thinking things.

24:06.862 --> 24:10.400
Perry, how many times have I told you
that Troop can ﬁnd his own sources?

24:10.574 --> 24:14.317
I told you it's not him.
It's just the guy from the eighth ﬂoor.

24:28.592 --> 24:31.208
Kent, what are you doing?

24:33.054 --> 24:34.464
This is my desk.

24:34.723 --> 24:38.966
Not for years, unless
somebody's been seriously demoted.

24:39.144 --> 24:40.224
Years?

24:48.904 --> 24:51.236
Clark? What are you doing?

24:51.406 --> 24:52.771
Lois, we need to talk.

24:57.704 --> 24:59.569
Ugh. Gloat all you want.

24:59.748 --> 25:03.741
But those names are getting ﬂipped the
second the boys from ops do a ﬂy-by.

25:07.422 --> 25:09.003
Clark.

25:09.633 --> 25:12.966
Clark,
what is going on with you today?

25:13.136 --> 25:16.799
-lt's like you've never been here before.
-I haven't, Lois.

25:20.143 --> 25:21.383
I'm from another time.

25:22.229 --> 25:23.264
[SIGHS]

25:23.438 --> 25:28.432
No kidding? Clark, you're from a different
planet. That's not exactly a news ﬂash.

25:30.695 --> 25:33.607
-What did you say?
-I didn't mean to come off so Lois.

25:33.782 --> 25:35.943
It's just that sometimes
when you get pensive...

25:36.117 --> 25:39.780
...I know that you have the whole "last son
of Krypton" thing on your shoulders.

25:39.955 --> 25:41.616
But that's why you've got me, okay...

25:41.790 --> 25:45.282
...to remind you that if you were going
to land your spaceship anywhere...

25:45.460 --> 25:48.793
...you couldn't have chosen better
people to ﬁnd you than the Kents.

25:48.964 --> 25:51.171
So you need to snap out of it.

25:56.638 --> 26:01.223
Wait, I know what this is about.
I forgot again, didn't I?

26:02.477 --> 26:03.637
Our anniversary.

26:06.314 --> 26:08.305
Our anniversary?

26:08.733 --> 26:11.145
Oh, don't play dumb,
you always hold it over me.

26:11.361 --> 26:15.479
The day you told me.
The day you ﬁnally trusted me, it was—

26:15.657 --> 26:19.491
It was romantic,
and it was the perfect day and—

26:19.661 --> 26:22.152
Okay, I always forget about it
until the last minute.

26:22.330 --> 26:24.161
But I swear it is not until—

26:25.333 --> 26:28.166
See? I told you.

26:28.336 --> 26:30.201
So, what is it?

26:32.382 --> 26:34.043
Wait a minute.

26:34.259 --> 26:37.467
Oh, no. Kryptonite again.

26:37.679 --> 26:39.044
Look, l--

26:39.222 --> 26:40.837
Blue? Red?

26:41.016 --> 26:42.347
Not green.

26:43.226 --> 26:45.387
Please tell me it's not black,
that was a disaster.

26:45.562 --> 26:47.223
Look, I just--

26:49.107 --> 26:50.688
I need the Legion ring.

26:50.859 --> 26:55.102
-Lois, do you know where it is?
-ls that a joke, Clark?

26:55.280 --> 26:58.238
Touch it once, shame on you.
Touch it twice, shame on me.

26:58.992 --> 27:01.904
And actually,
I could really use it right now...

27:02.078 --> 27:05.411
...because we have to be on opposite
sides of town in 10 minutes.

27:05.582 --> 27:07.743
And unlike you, I have to drive.

27:07.917 --> 27:10.124
I can't keep the mayor waiting.

27:13.381 --> 27:16.794
-Lois, I'm not supposed to be here.
-I know, we're late.

27:17.052 --> 27:19.543
Late? Lois, I need to get back.

27:19.721 --> 27:21.712
Look, the Legion ring
is the only way to do it.

27:23.308 --> 27:25.094
:mm

27:25.310 --> 27:27.801
Okay, why don't you check
your trunk of tchotchkes at the farm?

27:28.021 --> 27:31.764
Isn't that where you keep your phantom
catchers and fortress disks and stuff?

27:31.941 --> 27:33.932
And if you need me, I'm there.

27:34.110 --> 27:36.317
No deadline is more important than you,
okay?

27:43.244 --> 27:45.030
Going up, you're going down.

27:48.458 --> 27:50.540
FUTURE CLARK:
She's a handful, isn't she?

28:11.106 --> 28:12.596
You're right on time.

28:12.774 --> 28:16.938
-You knew I'd be here?
-Time travel, think it through.

28:17.153 --> 28:19.485
Because you were me
when you went through this and I'm--

28:19.739 --> 28:21.479
Well done, my man.

28:21.741 --> 28:24.949
How did I become so uptight
and nerdy?

28:25.120 --> 28:28.612
No time to chat about how, where, why.
We've been through weirder things.

28:28.790 --> 28:31.452
-I need you on the roof.
-When did I start taking orders?

28:31.668 --> 28:34.626
There's a nuclear reactor
about to blow outside of town.

28:34.796 --> 28:38.288
-I can't be in two places at once.
-If you knew, why didn't you stop it?

28:38.466 --> 28:41.958
You never would've experienced all this,
and you never would have become me.

28:42.804 --> 28:45.011
Well, that's too bad.

28:46.474 --> 28:48.806
Roof, now.

28:51.521 --> 28:53.227
That's what I become.

28:53.398 --> 28:55.229
[CRASH]

28:55.900 --> 28:57.606
[PEOPLE YELLING AND CHATTERING]

29:09.831 --> 29:13.824
LOIS [OVER RADIO]: Mayday, mayday,
we 've lost control. We 're going down.

29:14.502 --> 29:16.709
Mayday, mayday.

29:18.798 --> 29:22.336
PILOT: Tower, this is November, zero, one,
niner, niner, whiskey.

29:22.510 --> 29:24.216
We've lost hydraulics.

29:24.429 --> 29:26.010
[ALARM BEEPING]

30:05.428 --> 30:07.259
What are you doing?

30:14.771 --> 30:16.227
I don't know what's gotten into you.

30:16.397 --> 30:18.809
There is a pilot
with a migraine when he wakes up...

30:18.983 --> 30:21.895
...who wishes you could have
at least thrown on the cape.

30:23.238 --> 30:26.651
Lois, you protected my secret.

30:33.248 --> 30:34.954
[SIRENS WAILING NEARBY]

30:37.293 --> 30:39.079
What else was I gonna do?

30:39.254 --> 30:43.088
I would do anything for you.
Hardly a news ﬂash.

30:46.386 --> 30:48.126
Thank you.

30:52.600 --> 30:55.307
Oh, you drive me crazy.

30:57.272 --> 30:59.103
I guess I should get going.

30:59.274 --> 31:03.017
Oh. Right, obviously.

31:03.194 --> 31:05.810
Busy day for a superhero.

31:07.699 --> 31:10.941
Don't be late,
dinner reservation's at 7.

31:17.625 --> 31:20.788
Not every man
is destined to ﬁnd a woman like Lois.

31:20.962 --> 31:23.328
She's deﬁnitely one of a kind.

31:24.132 --> 31:27.295
-I know why you sent me here now.
-I intended to be here with you.

31:27.468 --> 31:29.720
But you interfered with the ring.

31:30.221 --> 31:34.305
You wanted me to see how things
would be with Lois and ﬂying.

31:34.475 --> 31:38.138
I wanted you to see that your darkness
lies not only in dwelling upon the past...

31:38.313 --> 31:40.474
...but in fearing the future.

31:41.316 --> 31:43.807
I've always hoped my life
would be like this.

31:43.985 --> 31:47.819
With Lois. Well, with all of it.

31:49.157 --> 31:51.648
Lately, I've stopped believing
that it could actually happen.

31:51.868 --> 31:53.733
Well, that's up to you, isn't it?

31:54.203 --> 31:56.159
You don't need
to worry about the future, Kal-El.

31:56.331 --> 32:00.745
You can see that it's just ﬁne as long
as you shed the weight of the past.

32:02.170 --> 32:06.038
It's just, the next time you decide
to defy me...

32:06.215 --> 32:09.252
...don't strand me back
in the dark ages.

32:18.353 --> 32:20.184
GREG:
I have a message for Clark Kent.

32:20.355 --> 32:23.768
Yeah? How about, "Don't leave
your date with Punch Bowl Maddie"?

32:25.109 --> 32:27.191
Something tells me
it's for a good reason.

32:28.363 --> 32:30.820
You know, Clark is the reason
a lot of us are still here.

32:30.990 --> 32:32.025
Oh?

32:32.200 --> 32:36.864
I kind of got caught up in my web
of obsession, and he set me straight.

32:37.288 --> 32:40.701
It's not every place that
has a hometown hero like Clark Kent.

32:43.711 --> 32:45.872
That's the kind of guy he is.

32:46.047 --> 32:50.211
Just tell him. Tell him thank you.

32:54.722 --> 32:56.223
CLARK:
I guess you're right.

32:57.141 --> 33:00.383
I've been so buried
by the mistakes of my past...

33:00.561 --> 33:03.268
...and so worried about
the responsibilities of the future...

33:03.439 --> 33:05.225
...I lost sight of the present.

33:05.650 --> 33:08.392
A hero is made in the moment.

33:08.569 --> 33:12.653
Not from questioning the past
or fearing what's to come.

33:13.157 --> 33:15.569
Just remember that, Kal-El.

33:18.121 --> 33:20.112
[LIFEHOUSE'S "EVERYTHING"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

33:20.289 --> 33:25.249
And how can I stand here with you

33:25.420 --> 33:30.255
And not be moved by you?

33:31.134 --> 33:35.753
Would you tell me how could it be

33:35.930 --> 33:39.138
Any better than this?

33:39.308 --> 33:45.178
How could it be any better than this?

33:45.857 --> 33:47.142
SUSAN:
Thank you all for coming.

33:47.316 --> 33:50.524
We'll see you all back here
in another ﬁve years. Bak, bak, Crows.

33:50.695 --> 33:52.356
I'm
sorry

33:52.572 --> 33:55.780
That's okay.
Who wants a dance anyway, right?

33:55.950 --> 33:58.282
You saved me the blisters, Smallville.

33:58.494 --> 34:00.530
Besides,
I have an early deadline tomorrow.

34:00.705 --> 34:02.991
Why put off till tomorrow
what you can do today?

34:03.166 --> 34:07.159
-You're quite a handful, Lois Lane.
-Look who's talking.

34:16.012 --> 34:17.877
You were right, Dad.

34:18.056 --> 34:21.594
I never stopped blaming myself
for what happened to you.

34:26.147 --> 34:28.854
It was a way to not have to let go.

34:32.028 --> 34:34.986
That's exactly what I have to do
to move on.

34:37.200 --> 34:41.409
To get rid of the darkness of my past
I've been carrying around.

34:42.914 --> 34:45.781
To be there for the people
who need me now.

34:52.131 --> 34:54.417
You said to hold on to Smallville.

34:56.844 --> 34:59.335
I will, I won't ever forget.

35:02.517 --> 35:05.304
Because you'll be with me
no matter where I go.

35:08.397 --> 35:11.355
But I have to say
the one thing I never could.

35:27.333 --> 35:29.415
Goodbye, Dad.

35:43.724 --> 35:46.557
I promise
to be the man you knew I could be.

36:02.285 --> 36:03.946
WOMAN:
You're all set.

36:04.120 --> 36:07.112
DIRECTOR: All right, settle down, people.
We're close.

36:07.540 --> 36:13.501
CREWMAN: Okay, get ready, we're going.
DIRECTOR: And three, two, action.

36:13.671 --> 36:15.286
Good morning, Metropolis.

36:15.464 --> 36:17.841
We have a very special show
for you this morning.

36:18.009 --> 36:19.624
We have an exclusive interview...

36:19.802 --> 36:22.589
...with a very special guest
who needs no introduction.

36:22.805 --> 36:24.591
Metropolis' infamous bad boy...

36:24.765 --> 36:28.132
...and self-admitted practicing vigilante,
Oliver Queen.

36:28.352 --> 36:30.343
Or should I say the Green Arrow?

36:30.521 --> 36:34.184
-What's on your answering machine?
-Yeah, that's--

36:34.358 --> 36:37.395
It's not every day a billionaire admits
to parading around in leather...

36:37.570 --> 36:39.982
...playing cops and robbers. Why do it?

36:40.656 --> 36:43.568
Were you just getting bored sitting around,
counting your money...

36:43.743 --> 36:45.950
...decided to play dress up
and it just stuck?

36:46.120 --> 36:47.701
How does that work, exactly?

36:49.999 --> 36:51.455
Huh.

36:52.376 --> 36:54.753
I think our audience
would like some answers.

37:04.847 --> 37:06.758
I lost someone.

37:08.851 --> 37:10.261
She meant everything to me.

37:13.522 --> 37:15.262
So for that you want, what...

37:15.441 --> 37:18.308
-...a merit badge and special rights?
-No.

37:18.486 --> 37:20.192
No, you're right, I'm not special.

37:20.363 --> 37:22.820
This isn't about who I am,
it's about what I do.

37:22.990 --> 37:26.107
And I don't think I'm the ﬁrst
rich boy who felt that way.

37:26.285 --> 37:27.741
John F. Kennedy once said:

37:27.912 --> 37:30.153
"Ask not what
your country can do for you...

37:30.331 --> 37:32.447
...but what you can do
for your country."

37:35.002 --> 37:39.086
So now you're— You're comparing
yourself to a fallen hero of this country?

37:39.257 --> 37:42.420
Why not? He saw the hero in all of us.

37:43.344 --> 37:45.835
I'm not dwelling on revenge
for past atrocities...

37:46.013 --> 37:49.597
...or looking ahead to what I can
personally gain from a few tax breaks.

37:49.767 --> 37:53.305
Drilling oil wells in the ocean, putting up
razor fences to keep out immigrants...

37:53.521 --> 37:56.012
...who only want
what our grandparents wanted.

37:56.190 --> 37:58.055
In this world of armchair bloggers...

37:58.234 --> 38:00.691
...who created a generation
of critics instead of leaders...

38:00.861 --> 38:02.692
...l'm actually doing something.

38:02.863 --> 38:08.278
Right here, right now,
for the city and for my country.

38:14.250 --> 38:16.366
And I'm not doing it alone.

38:18.504 --> 38:20.290
You're damn right I'm a hero.

38:38.482 --> 38:39.858
[CH UCKLES]

38:48.617 --> 38:50.198
LOIS:
Clark?

39:05.926 --> 39:07.882
Not that I'm an interior designer...

39:08.054 --> 39:11.467
...but one of these things
doesn't exactly go with the other.

39:15.686 --> 39:18.018
I'm sorry we missed our dance.

39:20.024 --> 39:22.857
You don't need to worry about me,
Clark.

39:23.402 --> 39:28.192
If anybody understands deadlines
and urgent things, it's me.

39:29.492 --> 39:31.574
I'm not worried about you.

39:33.287 --> 39:34.993
I missed you.

39:35.748 --> 39:37.204
Oh.

39:38.417 --> 39:43.707
Well, I don't know, neither of us
are primed for Dancing with the Stars.

39:43.881 --> 39:47.715
And, speaking strictly as friends,
I don't know if this is such a good idea.

39:47.885 --> 39:50.922
Lois, get over here.

39:53.099 --> 39:55.681
I'm not sure
how we're gonna make this work...

39:55.851 --> 39:59.218
...without the jukebox nostalgia
and the balloons and--

39:59.438 --> 40:01.815
-Lois.
-Shut up?

40:04.568 --> 40:06.399
Right, shut up. Ha.

40:09.240 --> 40:10.571
Ow!

40:11.492 --> 40:13.323
-Ah.
-Sorry.

40:13.494 --> 40:17.203
-l'm the one who put my feet under yours.
-Um, but l--

40:17.748 --> 40:20.706
-lt's ﬁne.
-Let's just try this.

40:39.728 --> 40:41.593
I love you.

40:43.774 --> 40:45.605
I love you too.

40:55.995 --> 40:57.860
Clark, there's something
we need to talk about.

40:58.038 --> 41:04.534
Just for now, can we leave tomorrow
till tomorrow and just have this?

41:04.712 --> 41:06.418
Mm-hm.

42:05.022 --> 42:07.013
[English - US - SDH]
